HEADWORD: Jejunum
<hw>Je*ju"num</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L.
<ets>jejunus</ets> empty, dry.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The middle
division of the small intestine, between the duodenum and ileum; -- so
called because usually found empty after death.</def>⟦br⟧
